  <section>
    <h3>Basic styles</h3>
    <h4>Page</h4>
    <p>HTML and body have the color $color--text variable applied to it by default</p>

    <h4>Links</h4>
    <p>Links are <a href="#">coloured the primary colour</a> and have <a href="#">no text decoration</a> by default.</p>

    <h4>Buttons</h4>
    <p>Buttons are now in here by default with some appropriate font sizing / spacing etc. By default there is o-btn with a hover/focus style and a disabled style.</p>

    <a href="#" class="o-btn">Check out this thing</a>

    <h4>Forms</h4>
    <p>Lots of default styling has been added for most input types and for selects, submits, buttons and checkboxes / radios. See snippets.md for the markup for a radio / checkbox. Elements are again 100% width as they'd usually be in a container. They are only defined as [type="text"] not input[type="text"] because they become hard to override with classes with the latter specificity.</p>

    <style>
      .cant-flex-on-fieldset {
        display: flex;
        flex-wrap: wrap;
        justify-content: space-between;
        align-items: flex-start;
      }

      .u-form-input {
        flex-basis: 49%;
      }

      .u-wide {
        width: 100%;
      }
    </style>

    <form>
      <fieldset>
        <div class="cant-flex-on-fieldset">
          <div class="u-form-input">
            <label for="name">Name</label>
            <input type="text" name="name" id="name" placeholder="Lando Calrissian" />
          </div>

          <div class="u-form-input">
            <label for="profession">Profession</label>
            <select name="profession" id="profession">
              <option>Please select...</option>
              <option>Cloud City Administrator</option>
              <option>Rebel Alliance General</option>
              <option>Professional Gambler</option>
            </select>
          </div>

          <div class="u-wide">
            <label for="reason">Reason for joining Rebel Alliance</label>
            <textarea name="reason" id="reason" placeholder="e.g. A deal was altered and I had to pray it wasn't altered further."></textarea>
          </div>

          <div>
            <label for="check">
              <input type="checkbox" id="check">
              <span>Check here to consent to becoming a known enemy of the Galactic Empire.</span>
            </label>
          </div>
        </div>
      </fieldset>

      <input type="submit" class="o-btn" value="Submit" />
    </form>

    <h4>Images</h4>
    <p>Block and 100% width by default as usually they'll be in a container or have their own class with a max-width.</p>
